'''Petar Musa''' ({{IPA|hr|pětar mûsa}}; born 4 March 1998) is a Croatian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[striker (association football)|striker]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[FC Dallas]] and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Zagreb]], Musa started playing football in the [[NK Hrvatski Dragovoljac|Hrvatski Dragovoljac]] youth system, before joining [[NK Zagreb]] in 2007.<ref name="union">{{Cite web|last=[[1. FC Union Berlin]]|date=1 February 2021|title=PETAR MUSA SIGNS ON LOAN|url=https://www.fc-union-berlin.de/en/union-live/latest-news/professional/Petar-Musa-signs-on-loan-622a/|access-date=8 June 2022|website=slavia.cz|language=cs}}</ref> He made his first team debut on 1 March 2016 in the [[Croatian First Football League|Prva HNL]] in a 3–0 away loss to [[Slaven Belupo]].<ref name="union"/> Musa eventually made six appearances for his team, as they were relegated to the [[Croatian Second Football League|2. HNL]].<ref name="union"/>

===Slavia Prague===
Musa was signed by [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] in 2017, but he was immediately loaned out to [[FK Viktoria Žižkov|Viktoria Žižkov]] in the [[Czech National Football League]].<ref name="union"/> He scored 12 goals in 37 games on loan, but during the winter transfer window, he was loaned to [[FC Slovan Liberec|Slovan Liberec]] in February 2019, making his debut in the [[Czech First League]] on 16 February in a 2–1 away loss against [[FC Baník Ostrava|Baník Ostrava]].<ref name="union"/>

During the first half of [[2019–20 Czech First League|2019–20]], Musa began displaying an impressive goalscoring form, scoring seven goals for his team, including a brace against [[BK Mladá Boleslav|Mladá Boleslav]] on 27 October, which led Slavia Prague to recall him from his loan and integrating him into the club's first team.<ref name="topscorer">{{Cite web|last=[[Slavia Prague]]|date=25 July 2020|title=Petar Musa králem střelců 2019/20|url=https://www.slavia.cz/clanek.asp?id=Petar-Musa-kralem-strelcu-2019-20-17674|access-date=8 June 2022|website=slavia.cz|language=cs}}</ref> In the league season, Musa scored Slavia's goal in the 1–1 draw to rivals [[Sparta Prague]] in the [[Prague derby]], the winning goal in a 1–0 away victory over [[1. FK Příbram]], netted a brace in the 4–0 home victory over [[FK Jablonec]].<ref name="topscorer"/> He finished the season as the league's top scorer alongside [[Libor Kozák]], with 14 goals. In doing so, he became the youngest ever player (aged 22 years and 122 days) to achieve that feat.<ref name="topscorer"/>

Despite being scouted by a number of established European teams, Musa decided to stay in Prague for another season in order to continue his development.<ref name="loans">{{Cite web|last=Croatian Sports|date=7 February 2022|title=Petar Musa: Croatia's Hottest Striker Right Now|url=https://croatiansports.com/petar-musa-croatias-hottest-striker-right-now/|access-date=8 June 2022|website=croatiansports.com|language=hr}}</ref> However, he fell into a scoring drought and was loaned for the remainder of the season to German [[Bundesliga]] side [[1. FC Union Berlin]] on 1 February 2021, at the last day of the 2020–21 winter transfer window.<ref name="union"/><ref name="kicker">{{cite web |title=Slavia Prags Petar Musa verstärkt die Offensive Union Berlins |url=https://www.kicker.de/spannender-spieler-musa-verstaerkt-die-union-offensive-796225/artikel |website=kicker |access-date=1 February 2021 |language=de|date=1 February 2021}}</ref> The loan fee paid to Slavia Prague was reported as €200,000 by sports magazine ''[[Kicker (sports magazine)|Kicker]]''.<ref name="kicker"/> On 17 April, he scored his first Bundesliga goal in a 2–1 home victory over [[VfB Stuttgart]],<ref>{{Cite web|last=[[Croatian News Agency|HINA]]|date=17 April 2021|title=VIDEO: Mladi Hrvat zabio svoj bundesligaški prvijenac, 'wunderkind' vodio Bayern do važne pobjede|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/bundesliga/video-mladi-hrvat-zabio-svoj-bundesligaski-prvijenac-wunderkind-vodio-bayern-do-vazne-pobjede-15066151|access-date=17 April 2021|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr}}</ref> but he added no more goals in 14 games for the rest of the season.<ref name="loans"/>

Instead of returning to Slavia Prague, Musa was sent on a season-long loan to Portuguese [[Primeira Liga]] side [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] on 25 August 2021, with an option to buy.<ref name="loans"/><ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]]|url=https://boavistafc.pt/petar-musa-boavistafc/|title=Petar Musa é o novo reforço do Boavista FC|date=25 August 2021|accessdate=21 September 2021|language=pt}}</ref> He scored 12 goals and provided four assists, helping his side to a 12th place finish, as Boavista triggered Musa's buyout clause of €3.5 million.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Mais Futebol|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica/petar-musa/benfica-entendimento-por-musa-vukotic-ruma-ao-boavista-em-definitivo|title=Benfica: entendimento por Musa, Vukotic no Boavista em definitivo|date=6 May 2022|accessdate=8 June 2022|language=pt}}</ref>

===Benfica===
[[File:Petar MusaSLB.jpg|thumb|upright|Musa with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2022]]
On 20 May 2022, Musa signed a five-year contract with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] of the same league, for a fee of €5 million, plus half of [[Ricardo Mangas]]' economic rights and [[Ilija Vukotić]] being sent to Boavista in part-exchange for €500,000 of half of his economic rights bringing the net cost of the transaction to €4.5 million.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2022/05/20/futebol-benfica-petar-musa-contratacao-oficial|title=Petar Musa é do Benfica!|date=20 May 2022|accessdate=20 May 2022|language=pt}}</ref>

He made his debut for the club on 23 August, replacing [[Gonçalo Ramos]] in the 52nd minute in the 3–0 home win over [[FC Dynamo Kyiv|Dynamo Kyiv]] in the second leg of the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Play-off round|2022–23 UEFA Champions League play-off round]], helping his side qualify to the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|date=23 August 2022|title=LESÃO DE GONÇALO RAMOS DÁ A ESTREIA A PETAR MUSA|url=https://www.abola.pt/amp/2022-08-23/benfica-lesao-de-goncalo-ramos-da-a-estreia-a-petar-musa/954062|publisher=[[A Bola]]}}</ref> Four days later, Musa made his league debut, against his former side Boavista, providing an assist and managed to win a penalty for his side after being fouled inside the box, which was subsequently converted by [[João Mário (footballer, born January 1993)|João Mário]] in a 3–0 win.<ref>{{cite web|date=27 August 2022|title=Bom trabalho de Musa e João Mário faz o segundo no Bessa (vídeo)|url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2022-08-27/liga-bom-trabalho-de-musa-e-joao-mario-faz-o-segundo-no-bessa-video/954559|publisher=[[A Bola]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=27 August 2022|title=João Mário bisa de penálti no Bessa (vídeo)|url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2022-08-27/benfica-joao-mario-bisa-de-penalti-no-bessa-video/954562|publisher=[[A Bola]]}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 8 October, closing a 4–2 home win over [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/benfica/detalhe/musa-este-golo-e-bom-para-a-minha-confianca?ref=Record%20Gaming_3BlocoAreasemDestaques|title=Musa: «Este golo é bom para a minha confiança»|publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|language=pt|date=8 October 2022|access-date=9 October 2022}}</ref> On 15 October, Musa scored the opener in a 1–1 draw to [[Liga 3 (Portugal)|Liga 3]] side [[Caldas S.C.|Caldas]] in the [[2022–23 Taça de Portugal|third round]] of the [[Taça de Portugal]], which Benfica went on to win 6–4 in a [[penalty shoot-out]], after [[Overtime (sports)|extra-time]].<ref>{{cite web|date=15 October 2022|title=Excelente trabalho de Musa para o golo do Benfica nas Caldas (vídeo)|url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2022-10-15/taca-de-portugal-excelente-trabalho-de-musa-para-o-golo-do-benfica-nas-caldas-vi/960756|publisher=[[A Bola]]}}</ref> On 2 November, he scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 6–1 away win against [[Maccabi Haifa FC|Maccabi Haifa]] in their last [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League#Group stage|2022–23 UEFA Champions League group stage]] match, to ensure Benfica's qualification to the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|round of sixteen]], as group winners.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/2894-benfica-crush-maccabi-haifa-to-snatch-top-spot-from-psg-in-group-h|title=Benfica crush Maccabi Haifa to snatch top spot from PSG in Group H|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Marshall|last=Matthew|date=2 November 2022|access-date=2 November 2022}}</ref> Over the course of the season, Musa remained a back up to first choice Gonçalo Ramos, as he only made substitute appearances, finishing the season with 11 goals in all competitions as he helped Benfica to win their first [[Primeira Liga]] title since 2019.<ref name="PLiga">{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/3242-benfica-crowned-champions-of-portugal|title=Benfica crowned champions of Portugal|publisher=PortuGOAL|last=Kundert|first=Tom|date=27 May 2023|access-date=27 May 2023}}</ref>

Musa started the [[2023–24 S.L. Benfica season|2023–24 season]], on 9 August, closing the 2–0 victory over [[FC Porto|Porto]] in the [[2023 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira|Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]], winning his second trophy with Benfica.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/id/berita/angel-di-maria-and-petar-musa-on-target-as-benfica-beat-porto-2-0-in-the-super-cup-38006246 |title=Ángel Di María and Petar Musa on target as Benfica beat Porto 2-0 in the Super Cup |publisher=OneFootball |date=9 August 2023 }}</ref>

=== FC Dallas ===
On 1 February 2024, Musa moved to [[Major League Soccer]] side [[FC Dallas]], where he signed a four-year contract, with an option for a further year, as a [[Designated Player Rule|Designated Player]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=1 February 2024 |title=FC Dallas Acquires Forward Petar Musa for Club-Record Fee |url=https://www.fcdallas.com/news/fc-dallas-acquires-forward-petar-musa-for-club-record-fee |access-date=1 February 2024 |website= |publisher=FC Dallas |language=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=1 February 2024 |title=Musa transferido |trans-title=Musa transferred |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2024/02/01/futebol-benfica-musa-transferencia-definitiva-fc-dallas |access-date=1 February 2024 |work= |publisher=S.L. Benfica |language=pt-pt}}</ref> The American club paid a club-record $9.7 million transfer fee, which could rise to $13 million with add-ons.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=1 February 2024 |title=FC Dallas sign Petar Musa from Benfica for club-record fee |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/fc-dallas-sign-petar-musa-from-benfica-for-club-record-fee |access-date=1 February 2024 |website= |publisher=MLS |language=}}</ref>

Musa made his debut for the club on 2 March against [[CF Montreal]] in the [[2024 Major League Soccer season|2024 MLS season]]. During stoppage time at the half, Musa scored his first goal for FC Dallas after a [[Video assistant referee|VAR]] check, with an assist from [[Bernard Kamungo]], in the 1-2 loss.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2 March 2024| title=Petar Musa! FC Dallas club-record signing scores in debut|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/petar-musa-fc-dallas-club-record-signing-scores-in-debut |access-date=2 March 2024|publisher=MLS}}</ref> On 19 June 2024, Musa recorded his first career [[hat trick]] in the 5-3 win against [[Minnesota United FC]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Vesely |first1=Sophia |title=Petar Musa suits up as hat-trick hero, powers FC Dallas' 5-goal surge vs. Minnesota United |url=https://www.dallasnews.com/sports/fc-dallas/2024/06/19/petar-musa-suits-up-as-hat-trick-hero-powers-fc-dallas-5-goal-surge-vs-minnesota-united/ |website=Dallas Morning News |date=20 June 2024 |access-date=20 June 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Musa began his international career with [[Croatia national under-18 football team|under-18 level]] in 2015, for a total of three [[cap (sport)|caps]]. On 14 November 2019, Musa won his first [[Cap (sport)|cap]] for the [[Croatia national under-21 football team|under-21 side]] in a 3–1 victory in [[Lithuania national under-21 football team|Lithuania]] for the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|2021 European Championship qualification campaign]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2026633/|title=Croatia vs. Lithuania}}</ref> In March 2021, Musa took part in the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], helping Croatia to a quarter-final finish, after losing 2–1 to [[Spain national under-21 football team|Spain]] in extra-time.<ref>{{Cite web|date=6 June 2021|title=Croatia vs Spain|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2031977/|access-date=8 June 2022|website=[[UEFA]]|language=en}}</ref>

He was called up to the [[Croatia national football team|senior side]] by manager [[Zlatko Dalić]] on 16 May 2022, for the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Austria national football team|Austria]], [[France national football team|France]] and [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/bola-branca/noticia/futebol-nacional/2022/05/16/petar-musa-chamado-a-selecao-da-croacia/284395/|title=Petar Musa chamado à seleção da Croácia|website=[[Radio Renascenca]]|language=pt|date=16 May 2022|accessdate=8 June 2022}}</ref> He made his senior international debut on 25 March 2023, replacing [[Marko Livaja]] in the 53rd minute of a 1–1 draw over [[Wales national football team|Wales]] in the [[UEFA Euro 2024]] [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|qualifiers]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/live/football/65002361|title=Euro 2024 qualifying: Croatia 1-1 Wales - reaction to late Wales goal|work=BBC Sport |date=24 March 2023}}</ref>

==Personal life==
His father Željko, is a [[Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian Croat]] hailing from [[Široki Brijeg]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/novi-dalicev-dragulj-nisam-slucajno-na-popisu-uzor-mi-je-mandzukic-a-mama-je-igrala-nogomet-1587995 | title=Novi Dalićev dragulj: Nisam slučajno na popisu, uzor mi je Mandžukić, a mama je igrala nogomet }}</ref>

